HEADWORD: Dinichthys
<hw>Di*nich"thys</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ terrible + <?/ fish.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
large extinct Devonian ganoid fishes. In some parts of Ohio remains of
the Dinichthys are abundant, indicating animals twenty feet in
length.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

